_json.gridTitle: 15 Heartwarming Things To Do In Herefordshire. This is one of England's most rural and sparsely populated counties, nestling between Wales, Shropshire and Worcestershire. Here you'll find the land of castles, black and white Tudor villages, the Mappa Mundi and cider making. Don't think it's all about the chill though. There's a big festival scene, off-roading, whitewater rapids and lots of walking trails and rambles. Come and check out this beautiful corner of England.
_json.description: 15 Heartwarming Things To Do In Herefordshire. From castles to black and white timbered houses, whitewater rapids, forest trails, and a lot of festivals, Herefordshire's a stunning and lesser known visitor destination. #VisitHerefordshire #Herefordshire  #England
